14 SECTION 2.
15 Article 1 of Chapter 1 of Title 40 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
16 general provisions regarding identification and regulation of motor vehicles and traffic, is
17 amended by adding a new Code section to read as follows:
18 "40-1-10.
19 (a) As used in this Code section, the term:
20 (1) 'Energy source' means any source of energy used for propulsion, powering, or other
21 functions of a motor vehicle or watercraft. Such term shall include, but shall not be
22 limited to, gasoline, diesel fuel, electricity, hydrogen, and solar power.
23 (2) 'Motor vehicle' means a self-propelled vehicle designed for use on public highways.
24 (3) 'Watercraft' means any vessel or craft designed for navigation on water, including,
25 but not limited to, boats and small crafts.
26 (b) No state agency or local governing body shall restrict the use or sale of a motor vehicle
27 or watercraft based on the energy source used to power the motor vehicle or watercraft."
28 SECTION 3.
29 Chapter 7 of Title 52 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to registration,
30 operation, and sale of watercraft, is amended by adding a new article to read as follows:
31 "ARTICLE 4
32 52-7-90.
33 As used in this article, the term:
34 (1) 'Commissioner' means the commissioner of natural resources.
35 (2) 'Department' means the Department of Natural Resources.
36 (3) 'Task force' means the Georgia Boating Access Task Force established pursuant to
37 Code Section 52-7-91.
