38 52-7-91.
39 (a) There is established within the department a Georgia Boating Access Task Force for
40 the purpose of ensuring safe and adequate boating access on any waters of this state. All
41 affected state agencies shall cooperate with the task force in its efforts to meet such
42 objective. This subsection shall not be construed to authorize the task force to perform any
43 function currently performed by an affected state agency.
44 (b) The task force shall:
45 (1) Coordinate with relevant local, state, and federal agencies to provide and enforce
46 boating access safety rules and regulations;
47 (2) Conduct evaluations of existing public boating access points to identify areas with
48 inadequate access and develop recommendations to address these inadequacies; and
49 (3) Identify, mitigate, and suppress threats from aquatic invasive species while
50 preserving boating access on any waters of this state.
51 52-7-92.
52 (a) The task force shall be composed of eight members as follows:
53 (1) The commissioner or his or her designee, who shall serve as the chairperson;
54 (2) One representative from the Association County Commissioners of Georgia, to be
55 appointed by the Governor;
56 (3) One representative from the Department of Transportation, to be appointed by the
57 Governor;
58 (4) One representative from the Georgia Municipality Association, to be appointed by
59 the Governor; and
60 (5) Four industry experts or stakeholders knowledgeable of the subject matter with which
61 the task force is concerned, to be appointed by the Governor.
62 (b) All members of the task force shall serve terms of four years and until his or her
63 successor is appointed. The commissioner shall make appointments to fill the unexpired
